The paper focuses on identifying and analyzing vulnerabilities in smart contracts, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of Solidity programming language and symbolic execution techniques, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The scalability of the proposed approach is also discussed, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
